	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would suggest either Highpass Hold, as mentioned earlier, or Crushbone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some people may think Crushbone is dumb, but if you fight there, be sure to loot crushbone pads and belts.  Those can be sold in GFay for 1pp per belt, and up to 4pp per pad.  If you want, you can just run to Kaladim and turn them into a certain guy there for great exp.  In Crushbone, at lvl 16 try to get a group in the Throne Room.  Other small little perks in Crushbone are that you can get many good items like: a Dragoon Dirk off of Ambassador DVinn if you manage to kill him, (lvl 26) a Dwarven Ringmail Tunic off of Emperor Crush (lvl 18) if you kill a Warlord (lvl 16) you can get a Bracer of Battle.  The easiest orc with good loot would be the Trainer, who drops a Shiny Brass Sheild worth up to 20pp, or it can be used.  You can turn in certain items attained in CB to receive the screaming mace <br>(8 dmg, 35 dly, effect: screaming mace)  which procs at lvl 10.  Just watch out for trains, as they claim the most deaths in CB.  There are also slavers you can kill (lvl 8-10) who occasionally drop keys that can be given to certain slaves for ok exp and money.  The last good thing about CB, is that it is 1 minute away from Kelethin, which in fact has a Bard Guild.<br><br>Sorry for sloppy advice here, but I hope I got all fo the info.<br><br>Mandallin<br>Half Elf Bard of the 19th Level<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
